5000|$|Kaigama is {{currently}} President of the Nigerian Bishops' Conference and the also the President <b>of</b> the Episcopal <b>Conference</b> <b>of</b> West African <b>Catholic</b> <b>Bishops.</b> He is also {{chairman of the}} Plateau State-convened [...] "Interreligious Committee for Peace". Together with the late Emir of Wase, Alhaji Haruna Abdullahi, he {{has been involved in}} promoting mutual understanding between Christians and Muslims.|$|R
